  sodium: 2.2 g
  serving size: 551
---

Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} (no need to peel!) into wedges roughly the width of your index finger. Pick the @rosemary{4} leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks). Spread the wedges out on a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch}, @ground black pepper{} and the rosemary. Toss to make sure they're coated, then pop on the top shelf of your oven until crispy, about ~{35%minutes}.

Combine the @soy sauce{25%ml} and @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} in a #mixing bowl{}. Add the @21 day aged British rump steaks{2} and make sure it gets a good coating of the marinade. Cover and leave until it's time to cook.

> TIP: The longer you can marinate the steak, the more flavours it will pick up. But don't worry if you're in a hurry - it will still taste great!

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced into half moons). Halve the @red cabbage{1/2} lengthways, remove the root in the middle then cut into roughly ½cm wide slices. Put a splash of @olive oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat and add the onion. Cook until soft, about ~{5%minutes}. Add the @mustard seeds{1} and when they start to pop (this should only take ~{20%seconds}) add the cabbage. Cook until soft, another ~{5%minutes}.

When the cabbage has softened, add the @white wine vinegar{2%tbsp}, a sprinkle of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have some), a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @ground black pepper{}. Stir everything together and put a lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}). Cook for ~{5%minutes} on low heat. Then take the lid off the pan and cook uncovered for another ~{5%minutes}.

Add a splash of @olive oil{} to a #frying pan{} on high heat and when the pan is sizzling hot, add the steak (leave any excess marinade in the bowl, you'll use it later!). Cook for ~{3-4%minutes} on each side. Then remove to a #board{} to rest for ~{3%minutes} (keep the pan).

> Tip: This will give you a medium steak, but if you want it more well done, simply cook it for 2 more mins on each side.

Turn the heat to low-medium and add the remaining marinade to the frying pan, along with the @redcurrant jelly{25%g} and @water{100%ml}. Tip: Use a spoon to break up the jelly so it melts into the sauce. Cook the sauce for ~{2-3%minutes}. When it's thicker and smooth, take it off the heat. Cut the steak into 2cm slices and serve with the wedges, a good spoonful of red cabbage and a drizzle of sauce.